Noto Sans Myanmar UI Thin Regular (NotoSansMyanmarUI-Thin.ttf)

CFF

Alignment Zones

Check if nodes are close to a zone, but not in or touching it.

This is a TTF, but this test is only for CFF fonts.

Info

Noto Sans Myanmar UI Light Regular (NotoSansMyanmarUI-Light.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'NotoSansMyanmarUI-Light', Everything looks good.

Pass

Noto Sans Myanmar UI Light Regular (NotoSansMyanmarUI-Light.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Noto Sans Myanmar UI' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light' = NID 1 'Noto Sans Myanmar UI Light'.

Pass

Noto Sans Myanmar UI Regular (NotoSansMyanmarUI-Regular.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'NotoSansMyanmarUI-Regular', Everything looks good.

Pass

Noto Sans Myanmar UI Medium Regular (NotoSansMyanmarUI-Medium.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'NotoSansMyanmarUI-Medium', Everything looks good.

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Noto Sans Myanmar UI' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium' = NID 1 'Noto Sans Myanmar UI Medium'.

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Noto Sans Myanmar UI' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold' = NID 1 'Noto Sans Myanmar UI SemiBold'.

Noto Sans Myanmar UI ExtraBold Regular (NotoSansMyanmarUI-ExtraBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'NotoSansMyanmarUI-ExtraBold', Everything looks good.

Pass

Noto Sans Myanmar UI ExtraBold Regular (NotoSansMyanmarUI-ExtraBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Noto Sans Myanmar UI' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraBold' = NID 1 'Noto Sans Myanmar UI ExtraBold'.

Pass

Noto Sans Myanmar UI Black Regular (NotoSansMyanmarUI-Black.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'NotoSansMyanmarUI-Black', Everything looks good.

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Noto Sans Myanmar UI' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Black' = NID 1 'Noto Sans Myanmar UI Black'.
